# Rust Standards

- Preserve zero-cost data paths in hot raster/geometry loops; avoid unnecessary allocations in frame-time code.
- Keep `mod.rs` exports explicit and minimal to avoid leaking unstable internals.
- Validate index math and buffer bounds before unsafe operations or pointer-style access.
- Prefer small, composable functions with clear ownership/borrowing boundaries over monolithic render functions.
- Keep Python bindings (`*_py.rs`) thin and focused on argument conversion plus error mapping.
- Document assumptions in concise comments when math or memory layout is non-obvious.
